<paragraph id="666636D0A901F151FF3AFB69633B8E93" blockId="11.[136,1452,626,1517]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FF3AFB69666A8F8E" bold="true" box="[189,294,1238,1264]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FEA1FB6965C98F8E" box="[294,645,1238,1264]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sophoricola">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FEA1FB6965C98F8E" box="[294,645,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Pseudocercospora sophoricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be regarded as a new species based on its distinct phylogenetic position (
<figureCitation id="FEE22A55A901F151FF77FB4566788E6A" box="[240,308,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1918,1940]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,208,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-28@6.[182,1406,190,1894]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. A Bayesian inference phylogenetic tree of 59 isolates of Pseudocercospora. The tree was built using concatenated sequences of the ITS, ACT and TEF1-α loci, each with a separate model of DNA evolution. Species clades from Iran are indicated in green coloured blocks and species names in black text. Culture accession numbers are listed along with host plant (orange text) and place of origin (dark blue text). The tree was rooted to Passalora eucalypti (CBS 111318). Bayesian posterior probabilities ≥ 0.95 are indicated with colourcoded branches and scale bar indicates number of expected changes per site." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5146804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5146804/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). In the individual gene trees, it is distinguished in the ITS (sister taxon to 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FBE5FB44625A8E6A" box="[1122,1302,1274,1300]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ocimi-basilici">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FBE5FB44625A8E6A" box="[1122,1302,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">P. ocimi-basilici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), ACT (sister taxon to 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FF6CFAA066C68E46" box="[235,394,1310,1336]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="udagawana">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FF6CFAA066C68E46" box="[235,394,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">P. udagawana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and TEF1-α (sister taxon to 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FD50FAA0643A8E46" box="[727,886,1310,1336]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="udagawana">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FD50FAA0643A8E46" box="[727,886,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">P. udagawana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) phylogenies. In the combined tree (
<figureCitation id="FEE22A55A901F151FA93FAA162148E46" box="[1300,1368,1310,1336]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1918,1940]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,208,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-28@6.[182,1406,190,1894]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. A Bayesian inference phylogenetic tree of 59 isolates of Pseudocercospora. The tree was built using concatenated sequences of the ITS, ACT and TEF1-α loci, each with a separate model of DNA evolution. Species clades from Iran are indicated in green coloured blocks and species names in black text. Culture accession numbers are listed along with host plant (orange text) and place of origin (dark blue text). The tree was rooted to Passalora eucalypti (CBS 111318). Bayesian posterior probabilities ≥ 0.95 are indicated with colourcoded branches and scale bar indicates number of expected changes per site." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5146804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5146804/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), it is a sister taxon to 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FEABFAFC66878E22" box="[300,459,1346,1372]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="udagawana">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FEABFAFC66878E22" box="[300,459,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">P. udagawana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FE5EFAFD64798E22" box="[473,821,1346,1372]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sophoricola">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FE5EFAFD64798E22" box="[473,821,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Pseudocercospora sophoricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically well distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FAAFFAFC661D8EFE" authority="(Guo &amp; Liu 1991)" baseAuthorityName="Guo &amp; Liu" baseAuthorityYear="1991" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sophorae">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FAAFFAFC62E78E22" box="[1320,1451,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">P. sophorae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="02484B21A901F151FF17FAD966058EFE" author="Guo, Y. &amp; Liu, X." box="[144,329,1382,1408]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" pagination="99 - 118" refId="ref12726" refString="Guo, Y. &amp; Liu, X. (1991) Studies on the genus Pseudocercospora in China V. Mycosystema 4: 99 - 118." type="journal article" year="1991">Guo &amp; Liu 1991</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having narrower stromata, wider conidiophores which are mostly reduced to conidiogenous cells, slightly thickened and somewhat darkened conidiogenous loci and medium to dark brown, somewhat wider and longer, distinctly septate 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FECCFA1166ED8EB6" box="[331,417,1454,1480]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Conidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="11" pageNumber="260" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">conidia</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FDC3FA10658B8EB6" baseAuthorityName="Guo &amp; Liu" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[580,711,1454,1480]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sophorae">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FDC3FA10658B8EB6" box="[580,711,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">P. sophorae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms 
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FC91FA10642D8EB6" box="[790,865,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">in vivo</emphasis>
superficial hyphae with solitary conidiophores. This is the first species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FE60FA6D65FA8E92" box="[487,694,1490,1516]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Pseudocercospora" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FE60FA6D65FA8E92" box="[487,694,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Pseudocercospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<taxonomicName id="A1D94D53A901F151FCEAFA6D633D8E92" box="[877,1137,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuroides">
<emphasis id="54ADEAC2A901F151FCEAFA6D633D8E92" box="[877,1137,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Sophora alopecuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
